[test arith]

# gen35: arithmetic over numbers -- pulled by BoolQ #6 ("can an odd number be
# divided by an even number"). gen27/gen28 could only order magnitudes; this
# computes with them. Tiny operator set; literal numbers via parse_num. Integral
# results print as integers, non-integral compactly (Decision D-2026-06-15h).
> what is 2 plus 2?
< 4.
> what is 10 minus 3?
< 7.
> what is 4 times 5?
< 20.
# A non-integral result keeps its fraction.
> what is 1 plus 1.3?
< 2.3.
# Divisibility by integer remainder.
> is 9 divisible by 3?
< Yes.
> is 9 divisible by 2?
< No.
# Division by zero is refused, not crashed.
> is 8 divisible by 0?
< I can't divide by zero.
# Non-numbers are declined and fall through honestly.
> what is gold plus silver?
< I don't understand that yet.
